description: Kung Fu Panda 4 - In Theaters March 8This spring, for the first time in almost a decade, comedy icon Jack Black returns to his role as Po, the world‚Äôs most unlikely kung fu master, with a hilarious, butt-kicking new chapter in DreamWorks Animation‚Äôs beloved action-comedy franchise: Kung Fu Panda 4. After three death-defying adventures defeating world-class villains with his unmatched courage and mad martial arts skills, Po, the Dragon Warrior (Golden Globe nominee Jack Black), is called upon by destiny to ‚Ä¶ give it a rest already. More specifically, he‚Äôs tapped to become the Spiritual Leader of the Valley of Peace.That poses a couple of obvious problems. First, Po knows as much about spiritual leadership as he does about the paleo diet, and second, he needs to quickly find and train a new Dragon Warrior before he can assume his new lofty position. Even worse, there‚Äôs been a recent sighting of a wicked, powerful sorceress, Chameleon (Oscar¬Æ winner Viola Davis), a tiny lizard who can shapeshift into any creature, large or small. And Chameleon has her greedy, beady little eyes on Po‚Äôs Staff of Wisdom, which would give her the power to re-summon all the master villains whom Po has vanquished to the spirit realm. So, Po‚Äôs going to need some help. He finds it (kinda?) in the form of crafty, quick-witted thief Zhen (Golden Globe winner Awkwafina), a corsac fox who really gets under Po‚Äôs fur but whose skills will prove invaluable. In their quest to protect the Valley of Peace from Chameleon‚Äôs reptilian claws, this comedic odd-couple duo will have to work together. In the process, Po will discover that heroes can be found in the most unexpected places. The film features the voice talent of returning stars Academy Award¬Æ winner Dustin Hoffman as Kung Fu master, Shifu; James Hong (Everything Everywhere All at Once) as Po‚Äôs adoptive father, Mr. Ping; Academy Award¬Æ nominee Bryan Cranston as Po‚Äôs birth father, Li, and Emmy Award nominee Ian McShane as Tai Lung, Shifu‚Äôs former student and arch-nemesis. Oscar¬Æ winner Ke Huy Quan (Everything Everywhere All at Once) joins the ensemble as a new character, Han, the leader of the Den of Thieves.  Kung Fu Panda 4 is directed by Mike Mitchell (DreamWorks Animation‚Äôs Trolls, Shrek Forever After) and produced by Rebecca Huntley (DreamWorks Animation‚Äôs The Bad Guys). The film‚Äôs co-director is Stephanie Ma Stine (She-Ra and the Princesses of Power). In 2008, the Academy Award¬Æ-nominated 2008 inaugural chapter, Kung Fu Panda, became DreamWorks Animation‚Äôs highest-grossing original animated film and launched a franchise that has earned more than $1.8 billion at the global box-office.Social Handles:Facebook: www.facebook.com/kungfupanda Twitter: https://twitter.com/dreamworks Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/kungfupanda TikTok: https://www.tiktok.com/@dreamworks Website: https://www.kungfupanda.com#KungFuPanda

description: You are not prepared for what is to come. #DunePartTwo - Only in theaters March 1.The saga continues as award-winning filmmaker Denis Villeneuve embarks on ‚ÄúDune: Part Two,‚Äù the next chapter of Frank Herbert‚Äôs celebrated novel Dune, with an expanded all-star international ensemble cast. The film, from Warner Bros. Pictures and Legendary Pictures, is the highly anticipated follow-up to 2021‚Äôs six-time Academy Award-winning ‚ÄúDune.‚ÄùThe big-screen epic continues the adaptation of Frank Herbert‚Äôs acclaimed bestseller Dune with returning and new stars, including Oscar nominee Timoth√©e Chalamet (‚ÄúWonka,‚Äù ‚ÄúCall Me by Your Name‚Äù), Zendaya (‚ÄúSpider-Man: No Way Home,‚Äù ‚ÄúMalcolm & Marie,‚Äù ‚ÄúEuphoria‚Äù), Rebecca Ferguson (‚ÄúMission: Impossible ‚Äì Dead Reckoning‚Äù), Oscar nominee Josh Brolin (‚ÄúAvengers: End Game,‚Äù ‚ÄúMilk‚Äù), Oscar nominee Austin Butler (‚ÄúElvis,‚Äù ‚ÄúOnce Upon A Time‚Ä¶In Hollywood‚Äù), Oscar nominee Florence Pugh (‚ÄúBlack Widow,‚Äù ‚ÄúLittle Women‚Äù), Dave Bautista (the ‚ÄúGuardians of the Galaxy‚Äù films, ‚ÄúThor: Love and Thunder‚Äù), Oscar winner Christopher Walken (‚ÄúThe Deer Hunter,‚Äù ‚ÄúHairspray‚Äù), L√©a Seydoux (the ‚ÄúJames Bond‚Äù franchise and ‚ÄúCrimes of the Future‚Äù), Souheila Yacoub (‚ÄúThe Braves,‚Äù ‚ÄúClimax‚Äù), with Stellan Skarsg√•rd (the ‚ÄúMamma Mia!‚Äù films, ‚ÄúAvengers: Age of Ultron‚Äù), with Oscar nominee Charlotte Rampling (‚Äú45 Years,‚Äù ‚ÄúAssassin‚Äôs Creed‚Äù), and Oscar winner Javier Bardem (‚ÄúNo Country for Old Men,‚Äù ‚ÄúBeing the Ricardos‚Äù).‚ÄúDune: Part Two‚Äù will explore the mythic journey of Paul Atreides as he unites with Chani and the Fremen while on a path of revenge against the conspirators who destroyed his family. Facing a choice between the love of his life and the fate of the known universe, he endeavors to prevent a terrible future only he can foresee.Villeneuve directed from a screenplay he co-wrote with Jon Spaihts based on Herbert‚Äôs novel. The film is produced by Mary Parent, Cale Boyter, Villeneuve, Tanya Lapointe and Patrick McCormick. The executive producers are Joshua Grode, Herbert W. Gains, Jon Spaihts, Thomas Tull, Brian Herbert, Byron Merritt, Kim Herbert, with Kevin J. Anderson serving as creative consultant.Villeneuve is again collaborating with his ‚ÄúDune‚Äù creatives: Oscar-winning director of photography Greig Fraser; Oscar-winning production designer Patrice Vermette; Oscar-winning editor Joe Walker; Oscar-winning visual effects supervisor Paul Lambert; Oscar-nominated costume designer Jacqueline West. Oscar-winning composer Hans Zimmer is again on hand to create the score.Warner Bros. Pictures.

description: Star Jam with Sushin Shyam || Part 2 || RJ Rafi‡¥¶‡µÄ‡¥™‡¥ï‡µç ‡¥¶‡µá‡¥µ‡µÅ‡¥Æ‡¥æ‡¥Ø‡¥ø‡¥ü‡µç‡¥ü‡µÅ‡¥≥ ‡¥∏‡¥ø‡¥®‡¥ø‡¥Æ‡¥Ø‡¥ø‡¥≤‡µÜ ‡¥Æ‡µç‡¥Ø‡µÇ‡¥∏‡¥ø‡¥ï‡µç‡¥ï‡µç  ‡¥Ø‡¥æ‡¥§‡µç‡¥∞‡¥Ø‡µÅ‡¥ü‡µÜ ‡¥§‡µÅ‡¥ü‡¥ï‡µç‡¥ï‡¥µ‡µÅ‡¥Ç, ‡¥á‡µª‡¥°‡¥ø‡¥™‡µÜ‡µª‡¥°‡¥®‡µç‡¥±‡µç ‡¥Æ‡µç‡¥Ø‡µÇ‡¥∏‡¥ø‡¥ï‡µç‡¥ï‡µç ‡¥°‡¥Ø‡¥±‡¥ï‡µç‡¥ü‡µº ‡¥Ü‡¥Ø ‡¥∂‡µá‡¥∑‡¥Æ‡µÅ‡¥≥‡µç‡¥≥ ‡¥ú‡µá‡µº‡¥£‡¥ø‡¥Ø‡µÜ ‡¥ï‡µÅ‡¥±‡¥ø‡¥ö‡µç‡¥ö‡µÅ‡¥Ç, ‡¥§‡¥æ‡µª ‡¥ï‡¥Æ‡µç‡¥™‡µã‡¥∏‡µç ‡¥ö‡µÜ‡¥Ø‡µç‡¥§ ‡¥ú‡¥®‡¥™‡µç‡¥∞‡¥ø‡¥Ø ‡¥ó‡¥æ‡¥®‡¥ô‡µç‡¥ô‡¥≥‡µÅ‡¥ü‡µÜ‡¥Ø‡µÅ‡¥Ç ‡¥¨‡¥æ‡µª‡¥°‡µç ‡¥ó‡µç‡¥∞‡µÇ‡¥™‡¥ø‡¥®‡µç‡¥±‡µÜ‡¥Ø‡µÅ‡¥Æ‡µä‡¥ï‡µç‡¥ï‡µÜ ‡¥ì‡µº‡¥Æ‡µç‡¥Æ‡¥ï‡µæ ‡¥∏‡µç‡¥±‡µç‡¥±‡¥æ‡µº ‡¥ú‡¥æ‡¥Æ‡¥ø‡µΩ ‡¥™‡¥ô‡µç‡¥ï‡µÅ‡¥µ‡µÜ‡¥ï‡µç‡¥ï‡µÅ‡¥®‡µç‡¥®‡µÅ ‡¥∏‡µÇ‡¥™‡µç‡¥™‡µº ‡¥π‡¥ø‡¥±‡µç‡¥±‡µç ‡¥Æ‡µç‡¥Ø‡µÇ‡¥∏‡¥ø‡¥ï‡µç‡¥ï‡µç ‡¥°‡¥Ø‡¥±‡¥ï‡µç‡¥ü‡µº ‡¥∏‡µÅ‡¥∑‡¥ø‡µª ‡¥∂‡µç‡¥Ø‡¥æ‡¥ÇProduced By     : RJ RafiGuest Curation : Manu SatheeshSound                : Vineeth TNCamera             :  Amal Dev PD Edit                    :  Amal Dev PD  & Shiju KDDesign               :  Vibin Raveendran 0:00 Highlights 1:16 InterviewSushin Shyam (born 13 February 1992) is an Indian music composer, instrumentalist, and singer primarily associated with Malayalam cinema. He is also a founding member of the folk metal band The Down Troddence. His music contributions to notable films such as Varathan (2018) and Kumbalangi Nights (2019) have consolidated his standing in the industry. Notably, his work on Kumbalangi Nights earned him the Kerala State Film Award for Best Music Director in 2019.Sushin embarked on his journey as an independent composer with the film Sapthamashree Thaskaraha (2014), for which he crafted the background score. His vocal debut was facilitated by the film Neelakasham Pachakadal Chuvanna Bhoomi (2013), where he lent his voice to the song Thaazhvaram under the direction of composer Rex Vijayan. Sushin's range of work extends beyond music, encompassing acting roles in various films. Additionally, he has performed in several songs, including Aadharanjali from Romancham (2022), a composition of his own.Sushin Shyam commenced his film career at the young age of 19, with Deepak Dev serving as his mentor. Over a span of four years, he assisted Deepak Dev in programming background scores for more than forty-five Malayalam, Tamil, and Telugu movies.[citation needed] His composition skills were showcased in the 2012 short film Oru kutti chodyam, directed by Ganesh Raj. The following year, Music Director Rex Vijayan enlisted Sushin's talent for programming the background score for Neelakasham Pachakadal Chuvanna Bhoomi. Sushin also lent his voice to a song, Thaazhvaram, for the film.Sushin's encounter with Rex proved to be a major turning point in his career. Encouraged by Rex, Sushin composed the background score for his next film, Sapthamashree Thaskaraha, in 2014, marking his first solo venture as a composer. In addition, he also sang the track Kayi Ethum Doorathonde for the film. Sushin's subsequent projects included composing the background score for Lord Livingstone 7000 Kandi in 2015 and for Kismath, directed by newcomer Shanavas Bavakkutty. He also created a song, Kissa Pathiyil, for the latter film, both of which were well received by audiences.In 2016, Sushin Shyam composed music for the short film Vicky, directed by Manu Joseph. The following year, he contributed to the score and two songs, Thambiraan and Irulu Neelum Raave, for the horror mystery film Ezra directed by Jay.K. He then worked on the background scores for Villain and The Great Father the same year.In 2018, he was responsible for the songs and score of three films: Maradona, Lilli, and Varathan. Notably, his work on Varathan received significant attention.Sushin continued to make his mark in 2019 with releases like Kumbalangi Nights and Virus. In 2020, he collaborated with Jackson Vijayan to co-compose the background score for Anwar Rasheed's Trance.[28] During the same year, he composed for Kappela and also created the background score for Kilometers and Kilometers, featuring Tovino Thomas.In 2021, Sushin had several notable releases including Malik, Kurup, and Minnal Murali. The track Raheemun Aleemun from Malik, performed by eight-year-old Hida Chokkad from Malappuram, achieved significant popularity and virality on the internet. Both Sushin's music and Hida's rendition were met with high praise. Another song from the same film, Theerame Theerame, also charted highly in the year's hit lists.The crime thriller Kurup received mixed reviews, but Sushin's music and score were widely acclaimed. The soundtrack for the superhero film Minnal Murali also gained considerable popularity, with Sajin Srijith of The New Indian Express describing it as instantly addictive and reminiscent of Western retro hits. All four songs Sushin composed for this film were also well received.#sushinsyam A Club FM Production. All rights reserved.
